  "universal_guidelines": [
    "Avoid generic 'SaaS Blue'. Use Slate/Zinc greys with Safety Orange/Yellow accents.",
    "Use 'Chivo' for headings to give an industrial, robust feel.",
    "Dashboard layout must be dense (Bento Grid Mode B) - construction managers need data at a glance.",
    "Use 'Traffic Light' color coding for status (Green=Available, Yellow=Maintenance, Red=In Use/Broken).",
    "Buttons should be rectangular or have very small radius (rounded-sm) to feel 'engineered'.",
    "Add 'data-testid' to all interactive elements.",
    "Ensure high contrast for outdoor readability (WCAG AA+).",
    "Use 'sonner' for toast notifications.",
    "Do not use gradients for backgrounds; use subtle noise or flat colors.",
    "Inputs and cards should have distinct borders, not just shadows."
  ],
  "instructions_to_main_agent": "Implement the dashboard using the 'Swiss & High-Contrast' archetype. Focus on legibility and data density. The 'Machines' and 'Tools' sections should use the provided images as thumbnails in list/grid views. Use the 'Chivo' font for all headings. Ensure the sidebar navigation is collapsible for mobile responsiveness."
